* Re: Digital tune PS in B136 Rack 14 and 17
text: 1/5/22: Contined T/S Rack 17 for PPS channel A indication led not lit and found the 120Vac terminal missing a jumper. After the jumper across the terminal was added, an additional issue show up when try activate the circuit. Further T/S found two buss line on J3 (Pin C and Pin M) connector installed incorrect position. The two pins were swapped to corrrect position and the circuit is working properly. During local control testing, both power supplies on Rack 14 and 17, they having similar issue that could not turn-on/ramp up output voltage. Further test and troubleshooting will be continued tomorrow (1/6/22). CH/BL/ML

Shift Summary: Wednesday Day Shift
text: SUMMARY: Recovery from holiday shutdown. INJECTOR: Booster White Circuit capacitor bank work complete. Injector available from 12:00PM. SPEAR: Stored beam, coasting, all shift. Topped up from 250mA to 500mA at 12:30PM. Sustained injection rate of 48mA/min. 12G-QF1 Hi R topoff interlock fault would not reset. Finally, after about three hours running, it reset. Attempted topoff fills only to have 12G-QF1 fault again. Disabled Topoff and locked key in safe. CATERed to PEM. BEAM LINES: All open except for BLs 5, 15 for BL checkouts.
